Special needs trusts,

00:27:54.270 --> 00:27:58.670
SSI, everybody gets denied
for SSI the first time around,

00:27:58.670 --> 00:28:02.470
we encourage families
to appeal and reapply.

00:28:02.470 --> 00:28:05.120
We look at the IEP and encourage ITPs.

00:28:05.120 --> 00:28:06.850
In California the law says you must

00:28:06.850 --> 00:28:09.190
start talking about transition at 16,

00:28:09.190 --> 00:28:10.660
but there's nowhere that says that

00:28:10.660 --> 00:28:12.860
we cannot start talking about this sooner,

00:28:12.860 --> 00:28:14.923
and we encourage families to do so.

00:28:17.640 --> 00:28:19.840
Nothing about us without us.

00:28:19.840 --> 00:28:23.500
So I told you I'd talk a
little bit more about Annika.

00:28:23.500 --> 00:28:26.470
She is employed through
Global Down Syndrome

00:28:26.470 --> 00:28:28.900
Foundation Grant and this
is in partnership with the

00:28:28.900 --> 00:28:31.180
Down Syndrome Connection of the Bay Area.

00:28:31.180 --> 00:28:33.393
Job coaching is provided by Best Buddies.

00:28:33.393 --> 00:28:35.618
I always feel like I'm an octopus that's

00:28:35.618 --> 00:28:38.770
grabbing people and
bringing them together to me

00:28:38.770 --> 00:28:40.390
so that we can do this work together.

00:28:40.390 --> 00:28:42.240
I call our clinic strength in numbers

00:28:42.240 --> 00:28:44.540
and I hope the warriors
hear this and fund us.

00:28:45.999 --> 00:28:48.249
(laughter)

00:28:49.260 --> 00:28:51.130
She makes folders for all of our

00:28:51.130 --> 00:28:53.070
families with important information.

00:28:53.070 --> 00:28:55.890
She's our laminating queen
and has other clerical duties,

00:28:55.890 --> 00:28:58.500
and she actually brings
the folders to the families

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:00.340
at the end of the appointments,

00:29:00.340 --> 00:29:04.200
and I always comment on
how amazing it is that

00:29:04.200 --> 00:29:07.110
inevitably the child
with Down syndrome makes

00:29:07.110 --> 00:29:10.110
a beeline to Annika and hugs her and it's

00:29:10.110 --> 00:29:11.300
incredible.

00:29:11.300 --> 00:29:14.670
And we also build community,
again strength in numbers.

00:29:14.670 --> 00:29:19.280
We have had our 3rd annual
holiday party this year,

00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:21.083
and we make it bigger every year.

00:29:21.940 --> 00:29:26.477
And this could not happen
without the UC Berkeley

00:29:26.477 --> 00:29:28.580
volunteers that we work with,

00:29:28.580 --> 00:29:31.740
they actually created a Down
syndrome group on campus

00:29:31.740 --> 00:29:34.150
and next Thursday on
World Down Syndrome Day

00:29:34.150 --> 00:29:35.910
they'll be handing out stickers.

00:29:35.910 --> 00:29:38.730
One of my first volunteers
is in the audience today

00:29:38.730 --> 00:29:40.920
and it's just so incredible to see

00:29:41.890 --> 00:29:43.760
people get inspired about serving

00:29:43.760 --> 00:29:45.263
individuals with disabilities,

00:29:46.896 --> 00:29:49.180
and they also do a whole lotta work.

00:29:49.180 --> 00:29:50.240
We connect families,

00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:53.490
I always ask families is it
okay if I connect you with

00:29:53.490 --> 00:29:56.660
another family so that
you can give them support?

00:29:56.660 --> 00:29:59.100
And all families inevitably say yes,

00:29:59.100 --> 00:30:01.400
please please I wanna help.

00:30:01.400 --> 00:30:03.820
We're gonna have our
first annual spring fling,

00:30:03.820 --> 00:30:07.900
a collaboration with the East
Bay Regional Parks on May 4th.

00:30:07.900 --> 00:30:09.520
It's gonna be superhero themed and

00:30:09.520 --> 00:30:12.010
there's gonna be incredible things.

00:30:12.010 --> 00:30:14.540
And starting in April
we're gonna have monthly

00:30:14.540 --> 00:30:17.000
developmental groups in
collaboration with the

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:19.050
Down Syndrome Connection of the Bay Area.

00:30:20.070 --> 00:30:23.083
We cannot do this just
by ourselves as doctors.

00:30:25.760 --> 00:30:27.730
Formal shout out to the Down Syndrome

00:30:27.730 --> 00:30:29.010
Connection of the Bay Area,

00:30:29.010 --> 00:30:32.040
stop by their desk if
you have a chance today,

00:30:32.040 --> 00:30:33.610
they're outstanding.

00:30:33.610 --> 00:30:35.630
The Silicon Valley Down Syndrome Network

00:30:35.630 --> 00:30:37.760
'cause we are expanding serving kids all

00:30:37.760 --> 00:30:39.530
the way from Fresno to Humboldt,

00:30:39.530 --> 00:30:43.250
we also have to expand our
support network relationships.

00:30:43.250 --> 00:30:47.023
And they've also been incredible
in supporting our efforts.

00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:51.733
If you have a child that you wanna refer,

00:30:53.210 --> 00:30:55.713
some referrals comes from birth hospitals,

00:30:55.713 --> 00:30:57.940
it's a mixed model of primary care

00:30:57.940 --> 00:30:59.540
and consultative services.

00:30:59.540 --> 00:31:01.700
So I'm the primary care physician for

00:31:01.700 --> 00:31:03.700
about 60 kids with Down syndrome

00:31:03.700 --> 00:31:06.140
and then we provide consultative services

00:31:06.140 --> 00:31:08.840
so far for about 60 more kids.

00:31:08.840 --> 00:31:11.623
So we've grown a lot in
two and a half years.

00:31:13.311 --> 00:31:15.476
And because I'm a pediatrician,

00:31:15.476 --> 00:31:19.870
PMD, taking consults for
other primary care doctors,

00:31:19.870 --> 00:31:21.427
insurances minds are blown and

00:31:21.427 --> 00:31:24.350
sometimes we do get a
little bit of pushback

00:31:24.350 --> 00:31:26.780
but there's real exciting
movements so that

00:31:26.780 --> 00:31:29.640
soon we'll also be in the
genetics department at UCSF

00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:31.453
and able to take more patients.

00:31:32.900 --> 00:31:34.510
And this is my plea to you.

00:31:34.510 --> 00:31:36.730
If you wanna work with
me I wanna work with you.

00:31:36.730 --> 00:31:38.480
If you wanna help I want your help,

00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:40.430
I never say no to help.

00:31:40.430 --> 00:31:43.640
Contact me and we'll take
questions after the next talk,

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:44.693
which is me again.

